title: Compiler panic on missing .await when calling async fn returning T1<impl T2>

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code

```Rust
trait Responder {}
impl Responder for () {}

async fn status() -> Option<impl Responder> {
    do_status()
}

async fn do_status() -> Option<impl Responder> {
    Some(())
}
```


### Meta
**Fails (rustc panics) on stable rustc 1.64.0**

`rustc --version --verbose`:
```
rustc 1.64.0 (a55dd71d5 2022-09-19)
binary: rustc
commit-hash: a55dd71d5fb0ec5a6a3a9e8c27b2127ba491ce52
commit-date: 2022-09-19
host: aarch64-apple-darwin
release: 1.64.0
LLVM version: 14.0.6
```

**Works correctly (compilation fails without rustc panic) on rustc 1.67.0-nightly (11ebe6512 2022-11-01)**
```
rustc 1.67.0-nightly (11ebe6512 2022-11-01)
binary: rustc
commit-hash: 11ebe6512b4c77633c59f8dcdd421df3b79d1a9f
commit-date: 2022-11-01
host: aarch64-apple-darwin
release: 1.67.0-nightly
LLVM version: 15.0.4
```
